posts.title: الصايغ: لا يمكن بعد اليوم قيام مؤسسات دستورية لا تلتزم بالمبادئ الأساسية لقيام الدولة
posts.text:
وطنية - اعتبر نائب رئيس حزب "الكتائب اللبنانية" الوزير السابق الدكتور سليم الصايغ، في تصريح اليوم، "أن مفاعيل استقالة رئيس الحكومة سعد الحريري هي انهيار الصفقة الرئاسية ومعادلة الجيش والشعب والمقاومة وكذلك إتفاق معراب الذي لم يعد قائما".

وقال: "ان الصفقة التي أتت برئيس الجمهورية العماد ميشال عون الى سدة الرئاسة قد انهارت بالكامل، طبعا رئيس الجمهورية يبقى في موقعه وفق ما يقتضيه الدستور، إنما العناصر السياسية التي تكثفت بلحظة زمنية وأتت به الى الرئاسة قد تحللت جميعها. كذلك لقد انهارت معادلة الجيش والشعب والمقاومة كما اتفاق معراب الذي لم يعد قائما ولا نعرف الى متى يمكن أن يصمد إتفاق مار مخايل إزاء أزمة عميقة، ليست مجرد أزمة سياسية عابرة كما ليست ازمة حكومة مختلفة على سياسات عامة، بل هي سوء تفاهم كبير تاريخي بنيوي وآثاره ستكون بنيوية. وعلى الرغم من الدعوات الى الالتزام بالأصول الدستورية التي نؤيدها ونطالب بها دائما، لا نعرف إذا كانت كل هذه المناشدات يمكنها معالجة الزلزال الحاصل".

وتابع: "ان الوقت اليوم ليس للتشفي والتذكير بأننا كنا على حق في موقفنا من هذه الصفقة منذ البداية، كما أن الوقت ليس مناسبا للقيام بجردة حساب، إنما في الأساس لم نصدر بيانا سياسيا واحدا للمكتب السياسي الكتائبي دون أن نشير فيه الى الخلل الكبير القائم والى عدم إمكانية الاستمرار في هرطقة الفصل بين التلهي بالملفات الصغرى وترك المسألة الجوهرية السيادية جانبا".

وتساءل "عمن يمكنه تولي رئاسة حكومة في الوضع الحالي"، داعيا رئيس الجمهورية الى "اتخاذ موقف تاريخي ينقذ فيه البلاد ويصحح المسار".

وختم: "ليس المطلوب وليس من الممكن شطب "حزب الله" من المعادلة السياسية وهو مكون أساسي، ولكن لا يمكن بعد اليوم قيام مؤسسات دستورية لا تلتزم بالمبادئ الأساسية لقيام الدولة. القضية ليست بتغيير حكومي عادي، إنما نحن نرى في حزب الكتائب أن المخرج الوحيد يكمن بالعودة الى الشعب عبر الانتخابات النيابية حتى لو كان من المبكر اليوم البحث في مواقيتها وتفاصيلها، إنما جوهر المخرج يكمن في معرفة ما يريده الشعب ومعرفة موقفه من السلاح والاستقواء بالخارج واعتماد فائض القوة لفرض معادلة سياسية في البلاد".

posts.title: Fixes for state law on lane change approaching police/workers on roadway
posts.text:
Letter: Fixes for state law on lane change approaching police/workers on roadway Tuesday Nov 7, 2017 at 6:00 AM 

I too am mindful of highway worker safety, from those pushing wheelbarrows to police officers just feet and 65 mph away. But improving safety is no easy task on a system designed around conveying maximum traffic and heavily dependent on driver common sense.
Massachusetts tried, passing Chapter 89, Section 7C  eight years ago, although many are unaware despite widespread electronic signs that would better say explicitly, “Flashing lights on shoulder mean change out of the right lane” with the qualifier, “if it's safe to do so.”
While well intended, it's impractical, unenforceable and largely beside the point. Impractical because it delegates to every motorist responsibility for eliminating a highway lane at a moment’s notice. Contrast how formal lane closures are implemented with a veritable landscape of warnings per DOT standards.
Unenforceable because assessing the safety of a sudden lane change - a criteria against which guilt is measured - occurs within the mind of the enforcement target, and the state can’t read minds. Nor like a backseat driver may the state claim to know how a driver ought to judge surrounding traffic and maneuver.
While tragedy drove lawmakers to “do something,” a true fix requires a measured approach. Start by focusing on the actual problem, which is drivers drifting out of travel lanes toward nearby workers. Next examine proven tools for preventing it: rumble strips, locating stopped vehicles further off the highway, enforcement against impaired and reckless drivers, and yes public service messages. Being inventive Yankees, develop better tools.
David K. Elliott
Oxford

Von Florian Madl Wien – Wer das Rad der Zeit zurückdreht, wird sich die Augen reiben: Das Stubaital war 1991, vor allem aber 1992 zentraler Bestandteil der Österreich-Radrundfahrt. Höhe­punkt: ein Bergzeitfahren von Neustift zur Gletscherbahn. Und geht es nach Franz Steinberger, dem Direktor der Traditionsveranstaltung (seit 1947 jährlich durchgeführt), dann sollen die alten Zeiten bald wieder aufleben: „Es wäre toll, wenn wir anlässlich der Ö-Tour 2018 im Juli Werbung für die Heim-WM im September 2018 machen dürften. Die Verhandlungen mit den Tirolern laufen bereits.“ Der Plan: Zunächst geht es vom Tour-Start in Feldkirch (Vbg.) aus nach Fulpmes, der Heimat von Ö-Tour-Sieger Stefan Denifl. Tags darauf wartet die Etappe Innsbruck – Kitzbüheler Horn, ehe es nach Osttirol weitergeht und schließlich Richtung Wels, wo die Österreich-Rundfahrt 2018 endet. An guten Argumenten würde es Steinberger und seinem Team jedenfalls nicht fehlen, schließlich stehe man mit dem Spartenkanal Eurosport kurz vor einer Kooperation. „Über den Werbewert muss man sich damit keine Gedanken mehr machen.“ Die Routenführung bedingt angesichts des Starts in Feldkirch jedenfalls eine Etappe durchs Inntal – es sei denn, man weicht über Deutschland aus. Sollten nämlich die Bestrebungen des Ö-Tour-Managements nicht zum gewünschten Ergebnis führen – Lizenz- und Aufenthaltskosten für den Tour-Tross im mittleren fünfstelligen Bereich werden vom Etappenziel gestellt – gäbe es bereits eine Alternative: „Es besteht Interesse vom Münchner Olympiapark.“ Charme hätte die Streckenführung durch das Inntal alle­mal. Schließlich soll ein Teil der Etappe über den selektiven WM-Kurs von 2018 führen. Das wiederum könnte einige Asse anlocken, die nicht bei der Tour de France am Start sind. „Ich hoffe, die Verantwortlichen finden zusammen und Tirol ist beim 70-Jahr-Jubiläum der Ö-Tour vertreten“, kommentiert Denifl, der in seinem Team Aqua Blue Sports allerdings auch ein Kandidat für die Tour ist. Zweite Tour of the Alps endet in Innsbruck Die Tour of the Alps 2018 beginnt in Arco am Gardasee und endet in Innsbruck. Das gaben die Organisatoren des Radetappenrennens bei der Präsentation am Dienstag in Mailand bekannt. Die Rundfahrt durch das Trentino, Südtirol und Tirol wird bei seiner zweiten Auflage von 16. bis 20. April außerdem dem heuer verstorbenen Michele Scarponi gedenken. Der italienische Profi war im April nur wenige Tage nach seinem Etappensieg bei der Premiere der Rundfahrt auf der ersten Etappe in Innsbruck bei einem Trainingsunfall tödlich verunglückt. Die nächstjährige Nachfolgeveranstaltung des Giro del Trentino umfasst neuerlich fünf Etappen. Zunächst führt die Strecke an drei Tagen mit etlichen Bergwertungen durch das Trentino und Südtirol. Die vierte Etappe wird in Klausen gestartet und endet in Lienz. Das letzte Teilstück über 161 km von Rattenberg nach Innsbruck geht auf dem Tiroler WM-Kurs der Titelkämpfe im September 2018 in Szene.

When you have sat for hours either online or pressing redial trying to get tickets for your favourite band and it ends up in a fruitless experience - then sometimes a tribute band is the next best thing. 
And it’s good news for fans of Cleethorpes Fake Fest, which has confirmed it will return to Meridian showground next year - with tickets now on sale for the popular event. The annual toe-tapping, rock n roll festival is taking place on Saturday, June 9 from 12noon until 11pm. Read More 
Promising to be even bigger and better than this year’s show the organisers have announced they have doubled the line-up - offering six professional level ‘fake’ tribute bands. The marquee was rocking in 2017 to the sounds of the Clee Fake Fest (Image: Duncan Young) 
Bands include; Musest (Muse), The Fillers (The Killers), Green Date (Green Day), Kazabian (Kasabian), Total Stone Roses (The Stone Roses) and Really Hot Chili Peppers (Red Hot Chili Peppers). 
Set inside a giant marquee - so the weather can’t spoil things - you can rock out to your favourite songs at an affordable price - performed by tribute acts who really do look and sound like the artists they imitate. Read More Fancy experiencing a retro movie drive-in to watch a Christmas film? 
The fun event is suitable for all ages and is safe, secure, accessible and friendly - making it a real family event or group outing. And if the weather does behave, there will be a variety of stalls, children's rides, inflatables and face painting. A colourful fun-loving vibe at the 2017 Clee Fake Fest (Image: Duncan Young) Other features include: 
* Licensed bar - well stocked with chilled lager, cider, bitter, spirits, wines and soft drinks 
* Drink tokens - These are £3.50 each and are available from the token desk to the side of the bar. You can exchange tokens at the bar for one bar (alcoholic) drink or two soft drinks 
* Food - Independent traders will provide a range of food including pizza, burgers and jacket potatoes 
No camping is available at the site but car parking will be available at the Meridian complex. Tickets are available online only from the event promoter (Image: Fake Fest) Where can I get tickets? 
Children aged 0 to 9 years can enter for free (no ticket needed), when accompanied by a paying adult. There is a maximum of two children per adult. 
Under 16 year-olds must be accompanied by a paying adult to enter the festival. Those aged 16-17 years must show proof of age if entering the festival alone.

2017 yılının ikinci çeyreğinde yurt içinde ikamet eden 14 milyon 116 bin kişi seyahate çıktı. 
2017 yılının ikinci çeyreğinde yurt içinde ikamet eden 14 milyon 116 bin kişi seyahate çıktı. 
Türkiye İstatistik Kurumu (TÜİK), 2017 yılı ikinci çeyrek "Hanehalkı Yurt İçi Turizm" verisini açıkladı. Buna göre,Nisan, Mayıs ve Haziran aylarından oluşan ikinci çeyrekte, yurt içinde ikamet eden 14 milyon 116 bin kişi seyahate çıktı. Seyahate çıkanların bir ve daha fazla geceleme kaydı ile ülke içinde yaptıkları toplam seyahat sayısı bir önceki yılın aynı çeyreğine göre yüzde 46,7 artarak 17 milyon 731 bin seyahat olarak gerçekleşti. 
SEYAHATE ÇIKANLAR ORTALAMA 388 TL HARCADI 
Bu çeyrekte seyahate çıkanlar 110 milyon 512 bin geceleme yaptı. Ortalama geceleme sayısı 6,2 gece, seyahat başına yapılan ortalama harcama ise 388 TL oldu. Yerli turistlerin, yurt içinde yaptıkları seyahat harcamaları 2017 yılının II. çeyreğinde bir önceki yılın aynı çeyreğine göre yüzde 52,9 artarak 6 milyar 882 milyon 250 bin TL olarak gerçekleşti. 
Seyahat harcamaları, kişisel veya paket tur harcamaları olarak yapıldı. Bu harcamaların yüzde 91,8'ini 6 milyar 317 milyon 753 bin TL ile kişisel harcamalar, yüzde 8,2'sini ise 564 milyon 498 bin TL ile paket tur harcamaları oluşturdu. 
YAKINLARI ZİYARET AMACI İLE YAPILAN SEYAHATLER İLK SIRADA 
Seyahate çıkış sebeplerinde ikinci sırada yüzde 19 ile "gezi, eğlence, tatil', üçüncü sırada ise ile yüzde 5,5 ile "sağlık" yer aldı. 
Seyahate çıkanlar en çok arkadaş, akraba evinde kaldı 
Bu çeyrekte seyahate çıkanlar 84 milyon 411 bin geceleme sayısı ile en çok "arkadaş, akraba evinde" kaldı. Konaklama türlerine göre geceleme sayısında ikinci sırada 10 milyon 592 bin geceleme ile "kendi evi" yer alırken, "otel" 8 milyon 336 bin geceleme sayısı ile üçüncü sırada yer aldı.

Während sie auf seinen Tod wartete, wusch sie das Geschirr ab. Sie wurde zu lebenslanger Haft verurteilt. © Reuters/AAP/Dean Lewins (Symbolfoto) Sydney – Die TV-Serie „American Horror Story“ soll eine 20 Jahre alte Australierin auf die Idee gebracht haben, ihren Großvater zu töten. Sie wurde am Obersten Gerichtshof des Bundesstaats South Australia wegen Mordes zu lebenslanger Haft verurteilt, wie der australische Sender ABC am Dienstag berichtete. Die Enkelin soll drogen- und alkoholabhängig sein und eine Persönlichkeitsstörung haben. Die junge Frau erstach dem Urteil zufolge im August 2016 den 81-Jährigen in seiner Wohnung in Adelaide, um sein Privatvermögen im Wert von 100.000 australischen Dollar (66.000 Euro) zu stehlen. Nachdem sie viermal zugestochen hatte, soll sie das Geschirr abgewaschen haben, während sie auf den Tod des Großvaters wartete. Richterin: „Brutal, kaltblütig und leidenschaftslos“ „Dieser Mord war brutal, gleichgültig, kaltblütig und leidenschaftslos geplant“, sagte der Richter in seiner Urteilsbegründung. Die Frau sei eine Gefahr für die Gemeinschaft. Als Tatmotive nannte der Richter Habgier und ein „unnatürliches Interesse an Gewalt und daran, Menschen sterben zu sehen“. Dem Anwalt der Enkelin zufolge war die Tat von der Fernsehserie „American Horror Story“ motiviert. Die 20-Jährige war von einer Freundin zum Großvater begleitet worden, die draußen im Auto wartete und sich dort währenddessen schminkte. Sie wurde wegen Beihilfe zum Mord zu 13 Jahren und sechs Monaten Haft verurteilt. (APA/dpa) Schlagworte

Применяется для уплотнения соединений, работающих в средах: воды и пара нефти и нефтяных продуктов жидкого и газообразного кислорода, этилового спирта и т.д. Для повышения механических свойств паронит в некоторых случаях армируют металлической сеткой (полученный материал называют ферронит, но формально он должен бы называться паронитом марки ПА). Толщина прокладки должна быть минимальной, однако, достаточной для заполнения канавок и неровностей. При увеличении толщины прокладки повышается вероятность ее выдавливания, поэтому не рекомендуется ставить толстые прокладки. Для работы в районах с тропическим климатом прокладки изготавливают с применением фунгицидов. Прокладки из паронитов ПМБ-1 и ПК работоспособны в условиях тропического климата без дополнительных добавок. Hi Everyone
 
 
TRAIL RUNS FOR THIS COMING WEEK

WEDNESDAY 8 NOVEMBER 2017 
  
CRAG / CSAG / CWAG TRAIL RUN / SHUFFLE / WALK 
 
Date: Wednesday 08 November 2017 
  
Time: ready to go at 5.45 pm 
  
Leaders: Chris Whales (run), Sandy Young (shuffle), Gavin Mohammed (walk) 
  
Location: Bokkemanskloof / Vlakkenberg (see below, Directions) 
  
Route description: From the start at the Constantia Nek parking area (see below, Starting point and Directions), we head down the road for a few hundred metres and continue down the jeep track until we reach Blue Valley Ave, the turn into Bokkemanskloof; now we go up this path as far as the well-known path over Vlakkenberg, left to cross the stream, and then slog UP the rocky stepped path to the crest, down the other side, around Silverhurst Estate and along the Beau Constantia fence until we emerge behind Constantia Nek Harbour House / La Parada; finally, the last couple of hundred metres back up to the Nek parking area and a welcome rehydrate. Sunset is at 7.21 pm. 
  
Duration and distance: approx 90 mins, approx 8 km 
  
Shufflers: Sandy Young will lead a slower, more relaxed run, leaving from the same place at the same time, for the same approximate duration. Please note that the normal CSAG pace, whilst slower than the runner group, is intended to get the heart rate up and the lungs pumping, and provide a good work-out for those who, for whatever reason, don't run quite as quickly as they once used to. Shufflers are advised to bring/wear the appropriate kit (see below, Equipment). 
  
Walkers: Gavin Mohammed will lead the walkers on a BRISK walk, leaving from the same place at the same time, for the same approximate duration. Please note that the normal CWAG pace is quite fast â€" the walk is not intended to be a gentle stroll in the park; it will get the heart rate up and the lungs pumping, and provide a good work-out for those who, for whatever reason, don't run. Walkers are advised to bring/wear the appropriate kit (see below, Equipment). 
  
Starting point:  Constantia Nek parking area  (click for Google Maps) 
  
Directions: From the M3 (heading south or north), take the M41 Constantia/Hout Bay Main Road exit and head up to the Nek, or from the Newlands area take the M63 Rhodes Avenue past Kirstenbosch and Cecilia Forest all the way to the Nek. From Hout Bay, just head up the road to the Nek. Park under the pines across the road from the restaurant. 
  
Equipment 
â€"         headlamp/torch for your own comfort 
â€"         water/energy drink/munchies 
â€"         weather-appropriate clothing/gear: long-range forecast for 6 pm would have us believe itâ€™s going to be partly cloudy, no rain, 23 Â°C, light breeze S 10 kph 
â€"         personal medication (if required) 
â€"         something liquid for post-run rehydrate session 
â€"         warmer/dry clothing for the rehydrate session 
â€"         whatever else you personally need for comfortable, safe trail running 
  
Car guards 08 Nov â€" NO CRAG GUARDS, possibly the regular informal attendant 
  
PLEASE TAKE NOTE 
 
The latest emergency numbers being promoted by SANParks, TMNP, SAPS and all the others are 
City emergency — 021 480 7700: calls patched through direct to Joint Ops Centre and then routed to relevant responders Table Mountain National Park rangers — 0861 106 417: goes directly to Visitor Safety rangers; report anything suspicious or out of the ordinary, persons, objects, possible camp sites, bark stripping, etc etc

Time: Meet 17:45 to run 18:00 
Where: Altydgedacht Wine Estate

Friends and slow runners welcome.

RUN Details for Wednesday 8th November:
Constantia Nek
NEW Start time 18:00
All welcome
We run for 60min
R15 gets you an hrs entertainment and some Coke (drink)

Good sense of humour

No Pain No Gain ...for ex athletes and desperate wannabe athletes...can hurt occasionally
PAIN for the nutcases who get off on inflicting pain on their mates. 
  
THURSDAY 9 NOVEMBER 2017 
CELTICS THURSDAY SUMMER TRAIL RUNS 
On Thursday 9 th November we meet at Newlands Forest for the run to start at 18h00. We will do the Silvertree Trail Route. 
Meet in the parking area at the Parks Board office / helipad / firebase (the parking area is the main parking area off the M3 – 700 metres north of the big M3 / Blue Route intersection with Rhodes Drive / Newlands Avenue, and about 1.2kms south of the southern end of UCT). 

The route is undulating as it heads from Newlands Forest initially with a few uphills before linking up with the Silvertree Trail. We head along the Silvertree trail, before eventually cutting down into Kirstenbosch before heading back along the lower rollercoaster route into Newlands Forest. 

The distance is about 7,8kms. 
Fast, Fast-Medium, Medium and Medium-slow pace options available, each with an experienced group leader to cater for different speeds, so provided you can run a flat 10kms in less than 65 minutes, there will be a group for you. 
NB: PLEASE ALL DO YOUR BEST TO STAY IN YOUR GROUPS – MOST PARTICULARLY DO NOT RUN AHEAD OF YOUR GROUP LEADER. If you are new to the runs and unsure of the pace of the various groups, then rather run with a slower group initially.

SATURDAY 11 NOVEMBER 2017 
 
K-WAY VOB TRAIL RUNNING GROUPS 
 
LONGER DISTANCE GROUP 
  
JOIN THE MATES A4DABLE TRAIL CHALLENGE – Constantia Nek (see details below). 
  
TABLE MOUNTAIN TRAILERS (K-WAY VOB MEDIUM DISTANCE GROUP) 
 
VALLEY OF THE RED GODS / MACLEARS BEACON 
This week we explore the top of Table Mountain north of the dams. In order to allow more time on the top of the mountain we will park in Theresa Ave, Camps Bay which cuts out most of the Pipe track distance.
Rendezvous and Start Time 
We meet at the path off Theresa Ave, Camps Bay (see directions below) at 6:25am for briefing and sign in before starting at 6:30 am . 
Terrain and Distance 
All groups will run the same route at the start: Up the jeep track from Theresa Ave to the Pipe Track, turn left on to Pipe track and run about 300m before turning up Kasteelspoort. At the top of Kasteelspoort, the idea is to turn left and run along the path up to the junction with Echo Valley - about 4km. From here distances and times will be determined by the routes chosen 
Here the faster group will continue on to the top of Platteklip. Once there they will turn right and head for Maclears Beaon. After tapping the beacon (the highest point n Table Mountain), they will continue on to Smuts Track and run for about 1km till the junction to Echo Valley. At this point they turn right and at the 4-way junction turn left to run back towards the dams and then make their way back to Kasteelspoort and down to the cars. That is the general idea. There are a lot of different paths to take and these can be decided by the group on the day.
The medium group will turn right at at the Echo Valley junction and at the 4-way junction they left and run till they meet the Maclears path and turn right to Maclears. The choice then is to return the same way or to follow the Smuts Track loop (see map - dotted lines) . 
The Relaxed group will decide how far they want to go before turning back and returning the same way. They have the choice of turning back at the junction, going to the top of Platteklip (as per faster group route - 2 short ladders involved ) or to follow the medium group route to the 4-way junction or just go round the dams and skip the rest - depends on how the group feels! 
See attached map to follow convoluted explanations! 
Flowing undulating single track and jeep track plus the ascent/descent of Kasteelspoort .
Essential Equipment 
Water, whistle, warm, wind or waterproof top depending on weather, space blanket and some form of ICE contact 
Recommended Equipment 
Food, buff, first aid items
Important : Please remember to look behind you at every turn in the route to make sure the people behind you see which way you are going . 
Leaders and sweeps for each group will be appointed and will ensure that no-one is left behind. Please ensure that groups stay together and that no-one is left on their own . 
How to get there 
From Cape Town city side: To get to Theresa Ave, drive past the turn off to the cable car and continue down the hill. Take the third road left - Fiskaal Rd . Follow the road as it winds up the mountain becoming Francolin Rd and then Theresa Ave. At the top (around 23 - 25 Theresa Road) park on the sea side of the road taking care not to block any driveways or access points. The entrance to the jeep track is sign posted.
From Camps Bay side: Drive up Camps Bay drive and turn right into Fiskaal Road. Follow directions above

MATES A4DABLE TRAIL CHALLENGE – PLEASE NOTE THIS IS A SATURDAY RUN (11 NOVEMBER 2017) 
  
This is an annual MATES Club Run but all runners are invited.  The CEO will be participating this year (for the very first time) so the challenge is out there.  Who can beat the CEO   Don't be fooled by his excessive smoking and apparent disgraceful form at weekly club runs.  He has been showing signs of his old form recently.  Are you confident enough to take him on? 
  
Start Time and Place 
  
07h00 at Constantia Nek car park. 
  
Route 
  
Start off running ±200m down the tar towards Hout Bay and take the gate to the left which puts you on the path that goes behind La Parade and up alongside the Beau Constantia fence.  Over Vlakkenberg to tar road and turn right.  ±100m up the tar road take the path right down past the Manganese Mine.  Take the contour left into Blackburn Ravine.  Up to the top of Blackburn Ravine.  Carry straight on up to the Constantiaberg Mast.  Down the tar road to the third path left, which you take.  At the crossroad, turn right and back over Vlakkenberg to Constantia Nek. 
  
Distance 
  
About 20km.  Please note that the section down past Elephants Eye and along Level 6 of Tokai Forest will not be done this year due to fire damage to the Level 6 path. 
  
Notes: 
• Take your own water and snacks.
• All runners are welcome.
• You need to be completely self-sufficient. Carry everything you will need on the day. This includes a basic medical kit, space blanket, whistle, windproof (waterproof if it is raining) jacket, warm headgear if it's cold or sun protection if it's hot. Charged cell phone with Mike's number (0823197250) stored as well as the City's emergency ops number (021 480 7700) and the SANParks Visitor Safety number (0861 106 417) programmed in. Just in case you need rescuing.
• You are also responsible for your own water and nutrition. There is little to no water on the mountain and, for the roadies, there are no water stations. You MUST carry your own.

More important:
Bring ice cold beers for after. 
  
  
  
SUNDAY 12 NOVEMBER 2017 
  
MATES RUN 
  
Start time: 07:00 from The Toad-In-The-Road pub in Lakeside (corner of Boyes Drive and the Main Road) 
  
Distance 15km-ish at a medium pace 
  
Run Leader 
  
Paul Whitmill 
  
Route Description: 
  
From the Toad parking lot run up Boyes Drive for about a kay and a half then turn right up to Muizenburg Peak. Go all the way to the beacon then down across the top of Farmer Peck's Valley to St James Peak. From St James Peak head towards Nellie's Pool. Cross two jeep tracks then head up Speciosa Valley, turn right past Tartarus Cave towards Crassula Path. Descend Crassula Path to the jeep track, turn right and go uphill for a wee bit. Just after the jeep track levels out, look out for single track to the left. Follow the single track to the jeep track below and turn right. Go uphill on the jeep track, past Junction Pool, towards the naval aerials and look out for a path to the left. Follow this path to an outcrop where the path turns to the right. Don't turn right (towards Higher Steenberg Peak) but instead go straight past the outcrop. The path pops out on the Wolfkop / Higher Steenberg Peak saddle. Turn right here and head up to Fat Lady Overhang. From here descend to the naval aerials, up and over the saddle, and back down to Boyes Drive and thence the Toad and ubiquitous beer.

A quick, rough guide to the Regular Weekly Trail groups in the first section of this email (K-Way VOB / MATES / CRAG / Celtics) 
There seem to be lots of new faces arriving at the weekly runs and from feedback received it seems it would be useful to clarify some basics and also advise which groups are suitable for which runners: 
The 4 groups referred to here are by no means the only clubs organisations that offer trail runs but these groups above are open to all runners , not just club members. There may well be other clubs that do this but we are not aware of them or they are not open groups. If you are looking for a club to join though then we would love to have you as a member at K-Way VOB. But It is not compulsory. For these 4 groups, there are no fees payable for attending the runs. They are free. The only costs you have to pay is where we have to pay entry fees to a reserve. These are for your account. There is no insurance involved. You run entirely at your own risk. You don't need to RSVP unless specifically requested. You just rock up and run. You may be required to fill in an attendance register at the run though. You are expected to know the general rules of trail running and which kit to wear and carry for the different weather conditions. If you don't know then you must ask. Which groups for which runners ? 
· K-Way VOB Longer Distance Group : (Not operating at the moment) Saturday mornings. All runners welcome. Not just for club members. This group is for more experienced, fit trail runners who can do 15km – 25km of technical, tough trail at a medium to medium fast pace. For more information contact Tim Bellairs on tim.bellairs@gmail.com . 
· K-Way VOB Table Mountain Trailers : Saturday mornings. All runners welcome. Not just for club members. There are three pace groups – 1. Main Group is a similar pace to the Longer Distance Group but for 10 – 15km and with more regroups than the Longer Distance Group which makes it do-able for some of the slower runners. 2. Recovery Group is a gentler pace for 7 – 10km suitable for recovering athletes and novice trail runners. 3. A walking group – not a stroll, but a brisk walk which has been known to bring walkers to near heart failure. For more info contact Peter Rogers ( p.d.n.rogers@gmail.com ). 
K-Way VOB Monday Evening City Bowl Group : Every second Monday evening from Kloof Nek car park. All runners welcome. Not just for club members. 8 – 10kms and most paces can be accommodated. Nothing too technical. For more information contact Tim Bellairs on tim.bellairs@gmail.com . · MATES : Sunday mornings, Tuesday Evening Time Trials and some night runs. All runners welcome. Not just for club members. Similar to K-Way VOB Longer Distance Group and often a little (or a lot) more hard core (extreme terrain) but definitely do-able for most experienced trail runners. Helps to be a beer drinker. For more info contact Michael Ohlsson on 0823197250. 
· CRAG / CSAG / CWAG : Wednesday evenings. All runners welcome. A pack run that caters for most trail runners. Not what I would call a beginner runner group as you need to be able to do 10 -15km of technical trail with confidence but once you have some base fitness then this is one of the first groups you need to join. Lots of experienced trail runners to advise you. The running group has recently been split in two. CRAG is the Faster Group and CSAG (Shufflers) is a slower running group. CWAG is the walking group for a brisk walk on the mountains. For more info contact Rod Prodgers at rodprodgers@icloud.com or Christo Steyn at trailrunner@sobonana.co.za or Ezan Wilson at ezanwilson@gmail.com . 
· Celtics : Thursday evenings. All runners welcome. Not just for club members. PLEASE NOTE THAT YOU NEED TO BE ABLE TO RUN 10km IN 65 MINUTES. 4 – 5 Pace groups which cater for just about all speeds from slow to super-fast. If in any doubt, start with the slowest group and work your way up over time. A great place to kick off your trail running although you do need some base fitness (must be able to run 10km) even for the slowest group. 
Each club / group has its own emailing list which you can join. This email just tries to draw all of the info together for convenience. 
 
Cheers 
  
The K-Way VOB Trail Team

posts.title: Queen Elizabeth Caught In Offshore Investment Scandal After £10 Million Fund Exposed In Leaked Paradise Papers
posts.text:
Louise Bonquin 
Queen Elizabeth invested private funds in offshore tax havens and this was exposed after the “Paradise Papers” emerged. Based on the leaked documents, the British Queen has millions of funds stored in the Cayman Islands and Bermuda. 
The controversial exposè was reportedly obtained by Süddeutsche Zeitung, a German newspaper. Aside from the Queen, many other rich and famous personalities were revealed to have been involved in the offshore investment, probably to avoid huge tax payments in Britain. 
The Duchy of Lancaster, the private estate that provides a source of independent income to the Queen, was said to have funds in the said territories that amount to £10 million or over US$13 million. 
Further, the leaked files showed that parts of the Queen’s money were invested in an account that was contributing to a chain with a bad record of irresponsible lending called BrightHouse and Threshers, a liquor store chain. Ultimately, the former went bankrupt in 2010 after owing the U.K. some £17.5 million in taxes. 
On Oct. 6, the Central Bureau of Investigation held a conference in connection with the Queen’s offshore investments. During the event, Jeremy Corbyn, chief of the Labor Party, said that “anyone who puts money into a tax haven to avoid paying tax should acknowledge the damage it does to society.” Leaked documents suggest that the private estate of Queen Elizabeth II invested $13 million in offshore tax havens https://t.co/0GtOyitzQ1 pic.twitter.com/jVWwy2rudf 
— CNN (@CNN) November 7, 2017 
The above statement was misquoted by the media, and it was reported that the labor leader was asking Her Majesty to issue a personal apology to the public for supposedly using offshore tax havens to evade tax. In a separate discussion, Corbyn clarified that as opposed to the reports, he did not specifically call out Queen Elizabeth to apologize for the matter but rather, his comment was for everyone involved. 
Now, in response to the news of a tax scandal involving the Queen, the chief finance officer of the Duchy, Chris Adcock, told BBC, “Our investment strategy is based on advice and recommendation from our investment consultants and appropriate asset allocation.” 
“We operate a number of investments and a few of these are with overseas funds. All of our investments are fully audited and legitimate,” the Duchy of Lancaster spokesperson added. 
Vanity Fair reported that the Queen might not be aware that her money was invested offshore. It explained that Her Majesty’s private estate is being managed by 18 staff members, so the Duchy can invest her funds without her knowledge. Nevertheless, the spokesperson for the Duchy firmly stated that the Queen voluntarily pays her tax on the income she receives from them. 
Finally, the big reveal in the “Paradise Papers” matters because the disclosure just shows illegal financial practice used by rich people. In the case of Queen Elizabeth, she is paying her tax although she is exempted from doing so. Her exemption makes her legally in the clear if an investigation for illegal investing in offshore tax havens would commence.

posts.author: TYCH
posts.title: [회로이론-16강의 V결선과 Y-델타결선변환]
posts.text:
회로이론 [회로이론-16강의 V결선과 Y-델타결선변환] 4시간 전 URL 복사 본문 기타 기능 번역보기 http://blog.naver.com/ggok777/221134655987 ▶제목: 회로이론-16강의 V결선과 Y-델타결선변환 이론 V결선은 일반적으로는 사용되지 않지만 변압기회로의 고장으로 문제가 발생하였을때 부득이 하게 사용하는 방법입니다. 델타결선에서 V결선으로 변환되어도 전류와 전압의 공급에는 문제가 되지 않는 것을 볼 수 있으며 V결선에는 선간전압=상전압 , 선전류=상전류 의 값이 같은 것을 알 수 있습니다. 회로이론에서는 V결선에 대해서는 크게 다루지 않지만 전력과 이용률 출력비 정도의 공식은 기억해둘 필요가 있습니다.
Y결선과 델타결선에서 전류와 전압의 크기가 같을때 저항의 비는 델타결선의 크기는 Y결선의 크기의 3배라는 사실을 알 수 있습니다. 그 밖에 Y에서 델타결선으로 델타결선에서 Y결선으로 바꾸는 공식은 사진의 공식으로 나타낼 수 있습니다.
마지막으로 전력을 측정하는 방법으로는 2전력계법이 있으며 이는 이론정도만 이해하시면 됩니다.
